The paper deals with sound event detection and separation using a time-frequency segmentation framework. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks and global weighted rank pooling for modelling the segmentation and classification mappings. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques for classification and segmentation, which could fall under cs.SI (Machine Learning) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the analysis of audio signals, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
